                     <interp inst="t18270913-350-victim2545" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>SECOND COUNT, stating them to be the property of 
               <persName id="t18270913-350-victim2546" type="victimName">
                  John 
                  Reed
               <interp inst="t18270913-350-victim2546" type="surname" value="Reed"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-350-victim2546" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-350-victim2546" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>WILLIAM BARKER. I am <rs id="t18270913-350-viclabel1948" type="occupation">carter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-350-victim2545 t18270913-350-viclabel1948"></join> to Thomas Wright, of Sawbridgworth. On the 16th of July I came to <placeName id="t18270913-350-crimeloc1949">Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-350-crimeloc1949" type="placeName" value="Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-350-crimeloc1949" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-350-off1946 t18270913-350-crimeloc1949"></join> with some lambs in my cart - there was a flat on the top of the cart, and as I crossed the market, with a load under my arm, I saw Smith leading my horse - I called to him to stop - he did so; I then missed the flat from the cart - it contained several things; I had received it from John Reed, to leave at the Ram Inn, Smithfield; Smith brought the flat back - I had not seen him take it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-350-person2547">
                  GEORGE 
                  BUSH
               <interp inst="t18270913-350-person2547" type="surname" value="BUSH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-350-person2547" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-350-person2547" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. On the 16th of July, about a quarter to four o'clock in the morning, I stood about forty yards from the cart, and saw Smith take the flat off at the corner of King-street - I ran down West-street, and saw Butler standing near the work-house in the street; Smith went up and spoke to him, and gave it to him: Smith saw me, and came up towards me; we came up to Smithfield, and he gave the flat up.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. CLARKSON. Q. Who is Butler? A. His father keeps a public-house in Smithfield; I do not know that the house is usually opened early; he had not got hold of Smith; he said, when I was taking them to the watch-house, that he had taken it from Smith, having stopped him with it - that was within a minute or two of the time. I ate nothing that was in the basket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-350-person2548">
                  SUSAN 
                  REED
               <interp inst="t18270913-350-person2548" type="surname" value="REED"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-350-person2548" type="given" value="SUSAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-350-person2548" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at Harlow, and am John Reed's brother. I know this gown and handkerchief; the other things have not been saved.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-350-person2549">
                  ABRAHAM 
                  GRIFFITH
               <interp inst="t18270913-350-person2549" type="surname" value="GRIFFITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-350-person2549" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-350-person2549" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I received charge of the prisoners. This gown and handkerchief were in the basket when it was opended at the office.</p>
               <p>SMITH's Defence. Butler knew nothing about it.</p>
               <p>SMITH - <rs id="t18270913-350-verdict1950" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-350-verdict1950" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
